1
00:00:00,626 --> 00:00:02,709
We enter the church through this door

2
00:00:03,375 --> 00:00:05,792
As a sign of respect for my faith and theirs

3
00:00:06,083 --> 00:00:09,751
I must touch this wall of the church, blessed

4
00:00:09,959 --> 00:00:11,042
This wall is blessed

5
00:00:11,209 --> 00:00:13,000
I say, in the name of the Father and the Son

6
00:00:13,250 --> 00:00:15,667
And the Holy Spirit, one God, Amen

7
00:00:15,667 --> 00:00:17,918
And I enter with them to the place of ritual

8
00:00:18,667 --> 00:00:19,709
In this place

9
00:00:19,959 --> 00:00:23,334
There were chairs here, and this was an aisle

10
00:00:23,792 --> 00:00:25,209
This is the aisle we enter from

11
00:00:25,626 --> 00:00:27,250
And we sit on the chairs, arranged chairs

12
00:00:27,417 --> 00:00:29,417
And the priest, <i>abouna</i> [our father] as they call him

13
00:00:29,459 --> 00:00:30,626
The priest is called <i>abouna</i>

14
00:00:31,042 --> 00:00:33,709
Because he represents their faith

15
00:00:34,584 --> 00:00:36,459
He stands on this pulpit

16
00:00:37,083 --> 00:00:39,250
This is the pulpit where the priest stands

17
00:00:41,292 --> 00:00:42,834
And the people sit here

18
00:00:42,876 --> 00:00:45,709
There were many, you know, on feast days they came

19
00:00:46,125 --> 00:00:47,125
And the priest here

20
00:00:47,417 --> 00:00:48,417
Reads the Gospel

21
00:00:48,626 --> 00:00:50,709
And we all stand in respect for the Gospel

22
00:00:50,959 --> 00:00:54,334
We rise and stand and read a verse from the Gospel

23
00:00:54,792 --> 00:00:56,959
And we read with them, then sit down

24
00:00:57,375 --> 00:01:00,375
And the priest speaks to us, may God preserve him

25
00:01:00,834 --> 00:01:02,209
He speaks to us about rituals

26
00:01:02,459 --> 00:01:04,250
And about what is permitted and forbidden

27
00:01:04,584 --> 00:01:07,417
Just like what the preacher tells us

28
00:01:07,751 --> 00:01:10,417
The same, they have forbidden things, don’t approach them

29
00:01:10,584 --> 00:01:12,751
Not allowed, you must respect the neighbor

30
00:01:12,959 --> 00:01:15,292
He used to say beautiful words

31
00:01:15,751 --> 00:01:17,834
Those words truly represented us

32
00:01:18,167 --> 00:01:20,459
Because they are honest, sincere, kind people

33
00:01:20,667 --> 00:01:24,250
So when those words came from their mouths, they came out beautifully

34
00:01:24,542 --> 00:01:27,250
Well-ordered, caring for every good person

35
00:01:27,584 --> 00:01:30,542
They had no enmity and carried no hatred toward anyone

36
00:01:30,959 --> 00:01:35,334
Their advice was beautiful, and advice was important to them

37
00:01:36,584 --> 00:01:40,042
Interviewer: Ahmad, do you know the purpose of these rooms?
Witness: Yes

38
00:01:40,083 --> 00:01:42,042
Interviewer: And why were they used? Please explain

39
00:01:42,042 --> 00:01:43,417
Witness: Yes, these rooms

40
00:01:43,834 --> 00:01:46,709
Were a library for books, the Gospel, and the Torah

41
00:01:47,167 --> 00:01:50,667
This was the library

42
00:01:51,125 --> 00:01:54,042
It was a library, but sadly they burned it

43
00:01:54,584 --> 00:01:57,417
This library was burned while ISIS was here

44
00:01:57,626 --> 00:01:58,834
And inside it

45
00:01:59,792 --> 00:02:01,417
This was a complete library

46
00:02:02,250 --> 00:02:04,709
And this was the pulpit where he sat

47
00:02:05,042 --> 00:02:06,375
They placed the cross

48
00:02:06,876 --> 00:02:10,709
And the items used for the Mass

49
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:12,542
And the Gospel, then continued

50
00:02:12,626 --> 00:02:16,167
And they placed the organ here, in this storage room

51
00:02:16,959 --> 00:02:20,626
And here was the statue of Our Lady Mary

52
00:02:21,334 --> 00:02:23,709
In this spot, right before my eyes

53
00:02:24,250 --> 00:02:27,042
Our Lady Mary the Virgin, peace be upon her

54
00:02:27,584 --> 00:02:30,584
So this was the ritual, and this was the priest’s place

55
00:02:31,334 --> 00:02:32,751
Yes, I have memories

56
00:02:32,959 --> 00:02:35,125
And this place was for storage

57
00:02:35,876 --> 00:02:39,167
They placed the offerings here, the offering place

58
00:02:39,626 --> 00:02:43,000
They fed the children and brought things to them

59
00:02:43,626 --> 00:02:45,209
This is the water basin

60
00:02:45,918 --> 00:02:49,500
This water was placed here to baptize children

61
00:02:49,959 --> 00:02:51,125
They wiped the child

62
00:02:51,209 --> 00:02:53,209
So he became a Christian

63
00:02:53,209 --> 00:02:55,959
Just like they purified us when we were children

64
00:02:56,167 --> 00:02:57,834
This was their purification

65
00:02:58,042 --> 00:03:02,751
They baptized the child, and when he came out,
they placed a sour-sweet candy in his mouth

66
00:03:02,959 --> 00:03:04,759
And that is how he was baptized and became a Christian
